TY  - JOUR
AU  - Darmouni, Olivier
AU  - Mota, Lira
T1  - The Savings of Corporate Giants
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae030
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 10
SP  - 3024
EP  - 3049
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We construct a novel panel data set to provide new evidence on how the largest nonfinancial firms manage their financial assets. Our granular data show that, over the past decade, bond portfolios have grown to be at least as large as cash-like instruments, driven by the meteoric rise of corporate bond holdings. To shed light on the drivers of this growth, we conduct a pair of event studies around the 2017 tax reform and the 2020 liquidity crisis. We find that large holdings of marketable securities are primarily driven by cross-border tax incentives, while cash-like instruments are driven by liquidity motives. (JEL G32, G35, G11, E440)
Y2  - 10/27/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae030
ER  - 



